One suspect was arrested following a search and seizure operation in which officials discovered a hydroponic dagga lab and a massive production of magic mushrooms. CAPE TOWN - Hawks members have swooped on an illegal drug facility worth a million rand just outside Cape Town. Officers made the discovery at Three Fountains Estate on Tuesday. One suspect was arrested following a search and seizure operation in which officials discovered a hydroponic dagga lab and a massive production of magic mushrooms. Hawks spokesperson Philani Nkwalase said: “A multidisciplinary team swiftly acted on information and conducted an intelligence-driven operation to dismantle the drug facility. The suspect, charged with drug dealing, is expected to be heard in the Atlantis Magistrates Court on Thursday.” 